en: Other large Attic skyphoi include New York 1982.11.16 (attributed by J. Robert Guy to the Painter of Brussels R330), h. .187 m., d. rim .360 m., w. with handles .51 m.; Louvre G 425 (ARV2, p. 929, no. 88), h. .30 m., d. rim .355 m.; and Louvre G 426 (ARV2, p. 888, no. 153) h. .325 m., d. rim .365 m. A red-figure skyphos of Corinthian type has been attributed to the Kleophon Painter (Mnzen, Sonderliste N, Mai 1971, pp. 48-50, no. 66).
H. 0.30 m., d. rim 0.332 m., w. with handles 0.478 m., d. foot 0.215 m.
On side A, the misspelled word kalos appears in the field between the top of the thyrsos and the female attendant's head.
